# 🎓 Virtual Learning Evaluation Model
### Predicting Student Success in Virtual Learning Environments Using the OULAD Dataset

---

## 📌 Project Overview

In the modern era of digital education, Virtual Learning Environments (VLEs) have become 
the backbone of online and blended learning delivery. Despite their widespread adoption, 
educational institutions often lack the analytical tools to objectively measure how 
effective their VLE is, which students are at risk, and what specific factors drive 
student success or failure.

This project addresses that gap by building a **machine learning-powered evaluation model** 
trained on the **Open University Learning Analytics Dataset (OULAD)** — one of the most 
comprehensive real-world educational datasets publicly available, containing anonymised 
records of **32,593 students** across **22 modules and presentations** from the UK's 
Open University.

Our model goes beyond simple grade reporting. It integrates **student demographics**, 
**VLE interaction behaviour**, and **assessment performance** to produce a holistic, 
data-driven evaluation of virtual learning success — one that can be directly applied 
by educational organizations to identify weaknesses, prioritize interventions, and 
improve student outcomes.

---

## 🎯 Project Objective

> **To design, build, and evaluate a machine learning model that predicts the likelihood 
> of student success in a Virtual Learning Environment, by analysing key behavioural, 
> demographic, and academic parameters — enabling educational organizations to measure 
> VLE effectiveness and make targeted, evidence-based improvements.**

