## 📂 Dataset — OULAD (Open University Learning Analytics Dataset)

**Source:** [https://analyse.kmi.open.ac.uk/open-dataset](https://analyse.kmi.open.ac.uk/open-dataset)  
**Institution:** The Open University, United Kingdom  
**Published by:** Knowledge Media Institute (KMI)

The dataset consists of **7 interrelated CSV files** that together capture the full 
learning lifecycle of a student:

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `courses.csv` | Module codes, presentation codes, and module lengths |
| `assessments.csv` | Assessment types (TMA/CMA/Exam), due dates, and weights |
| `vle.csv` | All learning materials available on the VLE platform |
| `studentInfo.csv` | Student demographics and final results |
| `studentRegistration.csv` | Registration and withdrawal dates per student |
| `studentAssessment.csv` | Every score submitted by every student |
| `studentVle.csv` | Every click made by every student on every VLE resource |

---

## 🔬 Key Success Parameters

After thorough analysis of the dataset and the literature on learning analytics,
we identified **15 key parameters** across three categories that our model uses
to evaluate VLE success:

---

### 👤 Category 1 — Demographic Factors

| # | Parameter | Source Column | What It Measures |
|---|-----------|---------------|-----------------|
| 1 | Gender | `gender` | Whether being male or female influences success rates |
| 2 | Age Band | `age_band` | Whether student age group (0–35, 35–55, 55+) affects outcomes |
| 3 | Region | `region` | Whether geographic location plays a role in performance |
| 4 | Highest Education | `highest_education` | Whether prior education level correlates with success |
| 5 | IMD Band | `imd_band` | Whether socioeconomic deprivation level impacts outcomes |
| 6 | Disability | `disability` | Whether having a disability affects a student's success rate |
| 7 | Previous Attempts | `num_of_prev_attempts` | Whether retaking a module reduces chances of passing |
| 8 | Credits Studied | `studied_credits` | Whether taking on more credits increases risk of failure |

---

### 🖱️ Category 2 — VLE Engagement Factors

| # | Parameter | Source Table | What It Measures |
|---|-----------|--------------|-----------------|
| 9 | Total VLE Clicks | `studentVle.csv` | Overall volume of interaction with the learning platform |
| 10 | Active Days | `studentVle.csv` | Number of distinct days the student logged into the VLE |
| 11 | Early Clicks | `studentVle.csv` | Clicks made in the **first 30 days** — strongest early warning signal |
| 12 | Activity Type Diversity | `studentVle.csv` + `vle.csv` | How many different types of learning content the student explored |

---

### 📝 Category 3 — Assessment Performance Factors

| # | Parameter | Source Table | What It Measures |
|---|-----------|--------------|-----------------|
| 13 | Average Assessment Score | `studentAssessment.csv` | Mean score across all TMA, CMA and Exam submissions |
| 14 | Average TMA Score | `studentAssessment.csv` | Coursework-specific average — most predictive of final result |
| 15 | Late Submission Rate | `studentAssessment.csv` | Proportion of assessments submitted after the deadline |

---

### 📊 Parameters Summary

| Category | No. of Parameters | Weight in Model |
|----------|--------------------|-----------------|
| 👤 Demographic Factors | 8 parameters | Background & context |
| 🖱️ VLE Engagement Factors | 4 parameters | Behavioural signals |
| 📝 Assessment Performance Factors | 3 parameters | Academic signals |
| **Total** | **15 parameters** | **Full prediction input** |

---

## 🤖 Modelling Approach

We trained and compared **three machine learning models** of increasing complexity:

| Model | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| **Logistic Regression** | Baseline — simple, interpretable benchmark |
| **Random Forest** | Advanced — ensemble of 100 decision trees |
| **XGBoost** | Advanced — gradient boosted ensemble, highest performance |

The final prediction is produced as an **ensemble** of Random Forest and XGBoost, 
giving a success probability (0–100%) for each student. Students are then classified 
into three risk groups:

- 🟢 **Low Risk** — ≥ 65% predicted success probability
- 🟡 **Medium Risk** — 40–64% predicted success probability  
- 🔴 **High Risk** — below 40% predicted success probability

